# Skill authoring (English)

Applies when creating or editing `SKILL.md` under any `skills/` directory.

## Language

- Write **`SKILL.md` in English**.
- Keep wording tight: short steps, tables over long prose — skills load into agent context.
- Frontmatter `description`: English, third person, WHAT + WHEN / trigger terms.

## Scope of this rule

- **In scope**: `**/skills/**/SKILL.md` only (not always-on — limits token load).
- **Out of scope**: companion templates used as runtime output mirrors, `AGENTS.md` / `CLAUDE.md`, issue/PR bodies, investigate/design artifacts.

## Output vs instructions

- Skill **instructions** = English.
- **Runtime artifacts** the skill tells the agent to produce (issue body, PR text, domain docs) follow **project** language rules (e.g. Vietnamese for user-facing issue/PR when `AGENTS.md` requires it).

## Checklist when adding a skill

- [ ] Frontmatter: `name`, `description`, `user-invocable` / `argument-hint` as needed (see `CLAUDE.md`)
- [ ] Instruction body in English; no Vietnamese prose in `SKILL.md`
- [ ] Prefer linking a short template file over inlining large examples
- [ ] Do not duplicate always-on narrative already covered by `AGENTS.md` or other rules
